  "body": "> /kind bug\r\n\r\nWhenever I try to change kube proxy metrics bind using flag `--metrics-bind-address=0.0.0.0`, it gives me:\r\n```\r\nOct 12 07:25:50 R11U2-7U20N-1 kube-proxy[510997]: E1012 07:25:50.358481  510997 server.go:661] starting metrics server failed: listen tcp: address 0.0.0.0: missing port in address\r\n```\r\nThen, I added the port `--metrics-bind-address=0.0.0.0:10249`, the error changes.\r\n```\r\nOct 12 07:25:58 R11U2-7U20N-1 kube-proxy[510947]: Error: invalid argument \"127.0.0.1:10249\" for --metrics-bind-address=0.0.0.0:10249: \"0.0.0.0:10249\" is not a valid IP address\r\n```\r\n\r\nI expect the metrics server to listen to 0.0.0.0:10249. Do I miss something?\r\n\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version: v1.7.8\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration**: on-premise\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release): debian/stretch\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`): Linux R11U2-7U20N-1 4.9.0-3-amd64 #1 SMP Debian 4.9.30-2+deb9u3 (2017-08-06) x86_64 GNU/Linux\r\n- Install tools: \r\n- Others:\r\n",
